testsuite.name: Scenario: Multiple class calendars opened

testcase.name: Given I am logged in as the default administrator
And I wait until the calendar has been loaded
And I clicked the calendar "month" view button
Then I assert the calendar displays the "month" view
When I create a "Master Class" event "Master Class Event" that starts "today" and ends "tomorrow"
Then I see a calendar event "Master Class Event"
When I create a "Demonstration Class" event "Demonstration Class Event" that starts "today" and ends "tomorrow"
Then I see a calendar event "Demonstration Class"
When I open a new tab on "Class Homepage" page of "Demonstration"
And I wait until the calendar has been loaded
Then I see a calendar event "Demonstration Class Event"
And I see no calendar event "Master Class Event"
When I open a new tab on "Class Homepage" page of "Master Class"
And I wait until the calendar has been loaded
Then I see a calendar event "Master Class Event"
And I see no calendar event "Demonstration Class Event"
When I switch back to "Demonstration Class" window
And I click the next button on the calendar
And I click the previous button on the calendar
And I clicked the calendar "month" view button
Then I assert the calendar displays the "month" view
Then I see a calendar event "Demonstration Class Event"
And I see no calendar event "Master Class Event"
And I close all the extra windows
